Introduction: Just when you thought it was safe to think the Twins might beat the Yankees — OK, let's be honest, nobody probably thought that, even with a 7-3 lead — things fall apart. Even after battering ace Gerrit Cole for five home runs, continuing a trend of knocking out Yankees pitchers, the Twins lost 10-7 Thursday and lost the series two games to one. Manager Rocco Baldelli was inclined to look at the positives, but the end result was more of the same. 12:00: Star Tribune Gophers football beat writer Randy Johnson joins the show to talk about a huge weekend of recruiting for coach P.J. Fleck and the program. 20:00: A curious decision by White Sox manager Tony La Russa — at least to a lot of us, though not to him — backfired in yet another Chicago loss. Listen and subscribe to the Daily Delivery: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google Podcasts | iHeartRadio The podcast archive is here. Questions? Comments? Long-winded diatribes about nothing in particular? E-mail me at michael.rand@startribune.com.  Follow me on Twitter @RandBall  and Star Tribune sports  @StribSports 